WorkItem.Description:
I am trying to upload and convert excel files generated with PHPExcel (latest version 1.7.6) to google docs. This works with .xls files but not with .xlsx files.
For xls files I use : 
$objWriter = PHPExcel_IOFactory::createWriter($this->excel_writer, 'Excel5');
and for .xlsx : 
$objWriter = PHPExcel_IOFactory::createWriter($this->excel_writer, 'Excel2007');
 
The error I get in google docs is : "The spreadsheet you are trying to upload is invalid." 
 
While looking around for a solution I noticed that the files posted as examples here : http://phpexcel.codeplex.com/wikipage?title=Examples (eg : http://www.codeplex.com/Download?ProjectName=PHPExcel&DownloadId=94244 or http://www.codeplex.com/Download?ProjectName=PHPExcel&DownloadId=94248 ) give the same error so I know the error is not from something in my code.
 
If you open any of the respective files with OpenOffice and "resave" them they are converted ok.
WorkItem.Summary: .xlsx upload and convert in google docs
